P3
# http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netpbm_format#PPM_example
#
# The P3 means the color data is in ASCII.
# The line below means 3 columns and 2 rows.
# The next line means 255 is the max color value, 
# Then the pixel data is six RGB triplets (in ASCII).
3 2
255
255   0   0
  0 255   0
  0   0 255
255 255   0
255 255 255
  0   0   0
